gomodel:SYNGO_4874  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3b: Immunoelectron microscopic detection of synaptophysin and G protein α-subunits in parallel fiber synapses of the rat cerebellum. Immunogold signals for Gαo2 (gene GNAO1, isoform Gαo2) and Gαq/11 concentrate in the vesicle cluster of the presynaptic terminals. Individual immunogold-labeled SSVs are indicated by arrowheads.. Experimental description: Figure 3: \"Immunoelectron microscopic detection of synaptophysin and G protein α-subunits in parallel fiber synapses of the rat cerebellum.\"\n\nantibody:\n\"Mouse monoclonal antibodies against synaptobrevin II (clone 69.1) (Edelmann et al., 1995) and against Gαo2 (clone 101.1) and rabbit polyclonal antisera against synaptophysin (G96; Jahn et al., 1985) and the vesicular GABA transporter VGAT (Takamori et al., 2000b) were kindly provided by R. Jahn (MPI für Biophysikalische Chemie, Göttingen, Germany)\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-11-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4874" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

